0
************************************************************************
* Task: Basic rules
************************************************************************
Keep the following naming convention rules:
1st char: Z
2-4 chars: your identifier, eg. starting letters of your name
5 char: '_' (fix underscore)
6 or 6-7 chars: identifier of the created object type
	DO: domain
	DE: Data element
	S: Structure
	T: Table
	V: View
7 or 8 char: '_' (fix underscore)
8- or 9- chars: descriptive name of the object

E.g. Domain for production order nr: Z_xx_DO_PRODUCTIUON_ORDER_NR

If ANY doubt would occur during the tasks, please, notice it, and let's talk about those later

Hints:
- When saving a new object (popup Create Object Directory Entry), click on button Local Object
- After activating a new object, switch to another object and then back to access further options, e.g. translation


1
************************************************************************
* Task: Create a domain with value table
************************************************************************
Create a new domain with value table (at this moment, the value table doesn't have to be entered)
domain type CHAR, 3 chars long
Description: Blaming text ID

Value table is to be defined later


2
************************************************************************
* Task: Create a domain with fixed values
************************************************************************
Create a new domain with fixed values
domain type NUMC, 2 chars long
Description: Source area of delaying
Possible values: 	01 - Production
					02 - Logistics
					03 - Vendor
					0A - Else

Translation of values to German is required, the text might be the same.


3
************************************************************************
* Task: Create data elements
************************************************************************
Create data elements for the domains defined in step 1 and 2.
Fill in Field labels accordingly
Translation of all texts to German is required, the text might be the same.


4
************************************************************************
* Task: Create database table for blaming text ID
************************************************************************
Create mandant dependent database table
Fields of the table:
mandant
ID of blaming text

Assign this table to domain of ID of blaming text. as value table


5 
************************************************************************
* Task: Create database table for blaming text
************************************************************************
Create mandant dependent database table for texts belonging to blaming text IDs. Language dependent.

hint: for the proper structure of the table, search for an example in the system for a table and realted text table

While creation, select field ID of blaming text and create a foreign key. If the field is properly entered, the foreign key has to be proposed by the system. If so, simply accept it.


6 
************************************************************************
* Task: Create maintenance view
************************************************************************
Create maintenance view for joined tables:
Blaming text ID
Blaming text

If foreign key in the previous step was properly set up, the 2 tables can be easily add to the view

Visible fields:
Blaming text ID
Blaming text



6
************************************************************************
* Task: Generate table maintenance view for ID of blaming text
************************************************************************
Generate table maintenance view for blaming text setup. (for the previously created view)

use authorization group OBSOLETE
A new function group has to be defined, which will contain the generated code and screens.
Object type identifier for function group is FG, e.g. Z_xx_FG_DDICTABM
One step maintenance, without recording routine.

hint: The system will generate the function group, and other objects, be aware of being local object, then just hit Enter to go forward
hint2: in ECC environment authorization group &NC& means no authorization check to maintian the table


7
************************************************************************
* Task: Create entries into the tables above
************************************************************************
Using the previously created table maintenance view, create entries via TA sm30.
E.g.
Blame Text ID		Blame Text
001					Dave does not find the hammer
002					Forklift is out of gas
A01					They mixed up the TOs again
L02              	Key of the forklift is lost
L03					AGV driver is on vacation
P01					Where is wrench?
P02					It is not my fault!

Translation of all texts to German is required, the text might be the same.

After entering texts and translations, check the content of the tables (e.g. via TA se16n)



8
************************************************************************
* Task: Create assignment of blaming texts and areas
************************************************************************
Create a database table to assign delaying areas and blaming texts
Create a maintenance view to fill in data into this data. 
Visible fields are:
Delaying area ID
Blaming text ID
Blaming text








